# Uploads

## Client (`uploadService.ts`)

- `uploadCsv(file, metadata, onProgress?)` → `POST /api/uploads/csv`
- `uploadPdf(files, metadata, onProgress?)` → `POST /api/uploads/pdf`
- Uses `XMLHttpRequest` for upload progress
- Validate before send: extension, size limits (25 MB CSV, 50 MB PDF batch)

## FormData field names

| Endpoint | File field | Metadata |
|----------|------------|----------|
| CSV | `file` | `datasetType` |
| PDF | `files` (array) | `docCategory` |

## Server

- CSV: `multer.single('file')`, store under `server/uploads/csv/`
- PDF: `multer.array('files', 20)`, store under `server/uploads/pdf/`
- Response: `{ uploadId, fileNames, storedPath(s) }`
- Validate mime/extension on server even when client validates

## Swapping to production

Replace disk storage and add auth middleware in `server/src/index.ts` without changing `uploadService` function signatures. Point webpack proxy or client base URL at production API.
